  "why": "The paper empirically demonstrates discovery of harmful/unsafe behaviors (steering outputs that can lead to potentially fatal collisions) across multiple real autonomous-driving DNNs, but it does not target or evaluate models that are equipped with explicit safety, policy, or security safeguards nor does it show bypassing such safeguards. The evaluation reports thousands of erroneous behaviors and example transformations that produce dangerous steering, yet the tested models are the Udacity challenge DNNs (steering-only) and the paper does not present or test any deployed safeguard mechanisms that were bypassed.",
